trend_summary: Across the series the river-adjacent core adds several new blocks and parking decks, while scattered infill houses and small commercial pads appear along main roads. No large subdivisions form; street grid and tree canopy stay mostly intact. Overall the district matures from lightly built to fuller, but remains a medium-density suburban landscape.
notable_changes: New multi-building complex added beside the river, replacing open ground/parking.
Several small infill houses and commercial pads inserted along the primary east-west arterial.
Widened arterial and fresh intersection realignment north-west of centre.
Conversion of an industrial parcel in the south-east to lighter commercial/warehouse roofs.
Slight increase in tree cover within residential blocks and along the river corridor.
